As agitation for the inclusion of more women in the administration of Bauchi State continues to mount, Bauchi State Governor, Sen Bala Abdulkadir Mohammed, has approved the appointment of Hajiya Amina Muhammad Katagum as Focal Person and Special Adviser, Social Investment Programme. The appointment was contained in a statement by Mukhtar Gidado, Senior Special Assistant on Media to the Governor, stating that Amina Muhammad Katagum was appointed to replace the immediate past Adviser who was recently elected as the member representing Gamawa federal constituency at the House of Representatives, Ahmed Madaki Gololo. ALSO READ: Air Canada to make emergency landing at Madrid Suspected armed militia kill, behead two farmers in Taraba SCOAN: Why the world must listen in 2020, beyond Moving beyond the prettiest culture for women Nigeria’s alarming security situation According to the statement, the newly appointed Adviser hailed from Zaki Local Government Area of the state and holds a Bachelor of Arts in Mass Communication and a Master’s Degree in International Affairs and Diplomacy all from Ahmadu Bello University (ABU), Zaria. It noted that Amina Katagum was a one-time Special Adviser on Women Affairs and Commissioner, Ministry of Commerce and Industry as well as Chairperson of many Boards and Commissions both within and outside the state. Hajiya Amina Katagum, a member of the Nigeria Institute of Management and a fellow of the Institute of Industrialist and Corporate Administration and her appointment is with immediate effect. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE. PREMATURE EJACULATIO